#what is shell

shell is a command line interpreter.Shell accept human readable commands from user and execute them.

#what is shell script ?

list of commands in order of execution is called shell script

we can write these commands in file as shell can take commands from file then execute them in shell avoide repetitive work 

There are various shells available :

1)Bash Shell(It is most widely used shell in linux systems and default login shell in linux )

2)C shell

3)Korn shell
===================================

How to determine the shell

echo $SHELL





